"title": "7471: temples, heathen",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7471: temples, heathen",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Other nations also built temples to their gods, and apostate kings of Judah and Israel were condemned for erecting heathen temples in their own countries.</p>\n<h2>Heathen temples</h2>\n<p>The temple of Dagon:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:28-Judg16:30\">JDG 16:28–16:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:2-1Sam5:4\">1SA 5:2–5:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:8-1Sam31:10\">1SA 31:8–31:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:18\">2KI 5:18</a> <em>the temple of Rimmon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:14\">NAM 1:14</a></p>\n<h2>Idolatrous temples in Israel and Judah</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:26-1Kgs12:30\">1KI 12:26–12:30</a> <em>Jeroboam's temples at Bethel and Dan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:32\">1KI 16:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:21\">2KI 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:23-2Kgs10:27\">2KI 10:23–10:27</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:17\">2CH 23:17</a> <em>A temple to Baal in Judah was destroyed in the reign of Joash.</em></p>\n<h2>The command to destroy pagan places of worship in Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:3\">DEU 12:2–12:3</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Holy things and holy places were used for pagan worship</h2>\n<p>Ahaz:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:10-2Kgs16:13\">2KI 16:10–16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:23\">2CH 28:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:4-2Kgs21:5\">2KI 21:4–21:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:5\">2CH 33:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:7\">2CH 33:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:7\">2CH 24:7</a> <em>Athaliah's sons used objects from the temple for the worship of the Baals</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:12-Ezek8:16\">EZK 8:12–8:16</a> <em>God showed Ezekiel a vision of people worshipping false gods in the temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16-2Chr26:20\">2CH 26:16–26:20</a> <em>Uzziah incurred judgment by usurping the priestly task of offering incense in the temple.</em></p>",
